  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    NEFFICS Service Modelling Editor: Service Journey Map modelling functionality&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;h4>&#xD;
    Creating a new Service Journey Map&amp;nbsp;diagram&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    To create a Service Journey Map&amp;nbsp;diagram from the workspace, the user needs to click on “Create New Model” and&#xD;
    select the appropriate diagram model. Figure 1 shows a corresponding screenshot. This will result in a new tab opening&#xD;
    in the browser with an empty diagram.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &amp;nbsp;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;resources/serviceml_editor_create_service_journey_map_diagram.png&quot; width=&quot;253&quot; height=&quot;404&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Figure 1: Creating a new Service Journey Map&amp;nbsp;diagram&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    As with the ServiceML functionality, the user can add Service Journey Map&amp;nbsp;elements in the diagram, by simply&#xD;
    drag-and-dropping the element from the toolbox to the diagram area. Quick Buttons can be used in order to create a&#xD;
    value flow between two roles.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h4>&#xD;
    Service Journey Map diagram example&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    A Service Journey represents a chronological mapping (from the customer point of view) of a service encounter. Figure 2&#xD;
    shows an example of a Service Journey Map diagram.&amp;nbsp;It contains the&amp;nbsp;ideal service journey for the AGR use&#xD;
    case.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &amp;nbsp;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;resources/serviceml_editor_service_journey_map_diagram_example.png&quot; width=&quot;600&quot; height=&quot;235&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Figure 2: Example of Service Journey Map diagram&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
